npm-packages/
# Leading slash anchors this to the repo root only. Without it, "tests/" would
# match every directory named "tests" at any depth (gitignore semantics) and
# exclude server/lib/tests/ and client/lib/tests/ too - which hid all the
# server-side Mocha *.tests.js suites from `meteor test` ("0 passing"). The
# root tests/ dir (Playwright + Node E2E specs) is not Meteor code, so keep it
# ignored - that also stops Meteor's file watcher churning on tests/playwright/test-results/.
/tests/
